data.name: Braised Short Ribs with Polenta
data.quickTastyDescription: Tender, flavorful short ribs served over creamy polenta for a comforting meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Season the short ribs with salt and pepper.
In a large oven-safe pot, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.
Sear the short ribs on all sides until browned, then remove them from the pot.
In the same pot, add the onion, carrots, and garlic, and sauté until softened.
Pour in the red wine and scrape up any browned bits from the bottom of the pot.
Add the beef broth, thyme, bay leaf, and return the short ribs to the pot.
Cover and transfer to the oven, braising for about 2.5 hours, or until the meat is tender. Check occasionally and add more broth if needed.
While the ribs are cooking, prepare the polenta according to package instructions.
Stir in butter and Parmesan cheese for creaminess before serving.
Once the ribs are done, serve them over the creamy polenta with the braising liquid spooned on top.
data.detailedName: Slow-Braised Short Ribs with Creamy Polenta
